         <abstract>
            <p>Let $\mathscr{K}$ be any real quadratic field and let $h_\mathscr{K}$ be the class number of $\mathscr{K}$. A method utilizing the $p$-adic class number formula for $\mathscr{K}$ is described for evaluating $h_\mathscr{K}$. The technique was programmed for a micro VAX II computer and run on all fields $\mathscr{K}$ with radicand $&lt; 10^6$.</p>
          </abstract>
